<h1>
<i><font size=+2>TUNA: Testing UNtyped Alleles</font></i></h1>
<img src="tuna.gif">
<p align="justify"><i>TUNA</i> is a free software package for estimating
allele frequencies for all the SNPs available in a population reference
panel (e.g. <a href="http://www.hapmap.org">HapMap database</a>) based
on genotype data from a subset of markers (e.g. the Illumina HumanHap300
BeadChip SNP set) in a group of subjects (e.g. the cases in a case-control sample).</p>

<p align="justify"><b>Current release:</b> version 1.1.2 beta (released in July, 2007)</p>

<p align="justify"><b>Download:</b> Please click <a href="package/TUNA.v112.beta.tar.gz">here</a> to download

<p align="justify"><b>Documentation:</b> <a href="tuna_doc.pdf">[PDF]</a>
<p align="justify"><b>Sample input files:</b> can be viewed and downloaded <a href="sample_file.html">here</a>

<p align="justify"><b>Questions and bug reports:</b> should be addressed
to wen at galton.uchicago.edu</p>

<p><b>References:</b><br> 
1.Nicolae DL (2006) "Quantifying the Amount of Missing Information in Genetic Association Studies". Genetic Epidemiology,
30(8):703-717.  [<a href="http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/cgi-bin/abstract/113310187/ABSTRACT">link</a>]<br><br>
2.Nicolae DL (2006) "Testing untyped alleles (TUNA) - applications to genome-wide association studies". Genetic Epidemiology, 30(8):
718-727a.  [<a href="http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/cgi-bin/abstract/113310193/ABSTRACT">link</a>]<br><br>
3.Wen X. and Nicolae DL (2007) "Case-control association studies of untyped markers with TUNA" Bioinformatics,doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/btm603.  [<a
href="http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/btm603">link</a>]<br>
 
</p>


